 A thriller called `` Child's Play,'' featuring a homicidal doll named <PERSON> Chucky </PERSON>, carved out first place in the nation's weekend box office sweepstakes with a take of $ 6.5 million Pesky pitchman <PERSON> Ernest </PERSON> <PERSON> P. </PERSON> <PERSON> Worrell </PERSON> -LRB- played by actor <PERSON> Jim </PERSON> <PERSON> Varney </PERSON> -RRB- teamed up with <LOCATION> Santa </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Claus </LOCATION> in `` Ernest Saves Christmas,'' an early holiday offering that was in second place with $ 5.7 million in its first week of release. `` Iron Eagle II,'' with <PERSON> Lou </PERSON> <PERSON> Gossett </PERSON> reviving his tough fighter pilot character, was third in formation with $ 3.5 million for its debut. `` They Live,'' director <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Carpenter </PERSON>'s exploration of yuppies as space aliens, was in fourth place with $ 2.7 million, followed by `` Everybody's All American.'' The movie about a football hero and his sweetheart earned $ 2.6 million. Several new movies are set for release this week in anticipation of large holiday audiences. They include `` High Spirits,'' `` 1969,'' `` Fresh Horses,'' and two animated offerings: <ORGANIZATION> Walt </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Disney </ORGANIZATION>'s `` <PERSON> Oliver </PERSON> and Company'' and the <PERSON> Steven </PERSON> <PERSON> Spielberg-George </PERSON> <PERSON> Lucas </PERSON> `` Land Before Time.'' Here are the top movies for the weekend as tallied by <ORGANIZATION> Exhibitor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Relations </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, with distributor, weekend gross, number of theater screens, average per screen, total gross, and number of weeks in release 1. `` Child's Play,'' <ORGANIZATION> UA </ORGANIZATION>, $ 6.5 million, 1,377 screens, $ 4,781 per screen, $ 8 million -LRB- five days -RRB-, one week. 2. `` Ernest Saves Christmas,'' <ORGANIZATION> Walt </ORGANIZATION> <ORGAN