<HEAD>Profile of the Palestine National Council</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-PLO, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ALGIERS, Algeria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <ORGANIZATION> Palestine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION> is a 450-member bicameral parliament-in-exile with members selected from <ORGANIZATION> Palestine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION> guerrilla factions and professional unions. The council elects the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION>'s ruling 15-man executive committee, sets out the committee's policy, distributes finances to the movement's seven departments and regulates relations with governments and other organizations. In short, it is the <LOCATION> Palestinians </LOCATION>' supreme decision-making body. The council is led by <PERSON> Sheik </PERSON> <PERSON> Abdel-Hamid </PERSON> <PERSON> Sayeh </PERSON>, a 78-year-old Moslem priest who was deported from the Israeli-occupied <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> after the 1967 <LOCATION> Middle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> war. The parliament is supposed to convene annually, but the executive committee may call special sessions for internal, regional or international developments. Another body, the Central Council, meets regularly. Its 70 members, who include the executive committee members, oversee implementation of <ORGANIZATION> PNC </ORGANIZATION> resolutions. The <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> council first was formed in <LOCATION> Jerusalem </LOCATION> in 1964. After the 1967 war when Israeli took control of the <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Strip </LOCATION>, 100 additional members were added to allow representation of the <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> area, which had been under Egyptian rule. When east <LOCATION> Jerusalem </LOCATION> was occupied, the council moved to <LOCATION> Cairo </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Egypt </LOCATION>, where it drafted the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> charter in 1968. Arab governments endorsed the guerrilla movement as the `` sole, legitimate representative of the Palestinian people'' in a summit the same year. After <LOCATION> Egypt </LOCATION> signed the Camp David peace treaty with <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> in 1979, the council moved out of <LOCATION> Cairo </LOCATION>. Since then, the <ORGANIZATION> PNC </ORGANIZATION> has held sessions in <LOCATION> Syria </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Jordan </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Algeria </LOCATION>. There are independent council members and those designated by <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> factions and unions such as those representing students, lawyers and women. Independents occupy 199 seats. The rest are distributed to the 10 unions and guerrilla factions. Council decisions also are made by majority vote. Fatah, the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION>'s largest faction which is headed by <PERSON> Yasser </PERSON> <PERSON> Arafat </PERSON>, has 55 seats, the largest block in the council. About 80 percent to 85 percent of the delegates are aligned with <PERSON> Arafat </PERSON>.
</TEXT>
