hic concentration camps scenes The unexpectedly low rating for `` War and Remembrance'' can be ascribed in part to <PERSON> Nielsen </PERSON>'s new measurement system that tends to produce lower ratings generally, but probably owes more to a general trend away from network viewing, a trend that was exacerbated when the writers' strike delayed the networks' new shows and summer reruns extended well into the fall. But network executives have been saying for the past few years that the days of the lengthy, big-event miniseries are probably over. Most miniseries in recent seasons have been no longer than four parts and most have been only two. `` Amerika,'' the last long miniseries at 14 -LCB- hours, also only <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>, failed in the ratings two years ago.
