<DATELINE>FORT LAUDERDALE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The 102 anti-abortion activists arrested for trying to block the doors of a women's clinic may end up paying the Police Department for costs incurred in handling the protest, the police chief said. Police Chief <PERSON> Joe </PERSON> <PERSON> Gerwens </PERSON> said Monday he had asked City Prosecutor <PERSON> Scott </PERSON> <PERSON> Walker </PERSON> to try to recover the estimated $ 3,800 the Nov. 4 protest cost the department. `` They chose civil disobedience to make a point and they should be willing to pay the consequences,'' <PERSON> Gerwens </PERSON> said. `` They planned on being arrested.'' Demonstrators planted themselves before the entrance to the Sigma Women's Center, which advertises abortions, waiting to carried to paddy wagons and booked on trespassing charges. It took 26 <LOCATION> Fort </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Lauderdale </LOCATION> police officers, plus eight from nearby <LOCATION> Oakland </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Park </LOCATION> and the <ORGANIZATION> Broward </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> County </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Sheriff </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Office </ORGANIZATION>, to quell the disturbance, <PERSON> Gerwens </PERSON> said. In addition to the officers' time, police cars had to be diverted from their assigned zones to handle the protest. Other costs included transportation, two portable toilets, film for booking prisoners, an emergency medical truck and an ambulance, he said. <PERSON> Bonnie </PERSON> <PERSON> Callahan </PERSON>, a spokeswoman for the anti-abortion organization Rescue <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION>, which was among several groups at the protest, called the plan to seek reimbursement unfair. Ms. <PERSON> Callahan </PERSON>, whose 13-year-old daughter was among those arrested, said the demonstration `` was not for the purpose of getting arrested or getting publicity. Our main reason was to save babies and save women from being exploited.'' All those arr