Monday. <PERSON> Kenyon </PERSON> granted the motion after several hours of argument. The judge noted that the trial had just begun and no evidence had been presented. `` It seems to me much cleaner'' this way, <PERSON> Kenyon </PERSON> said, adding he did n't want to take objecting parties `` kicking and screaming'' into the rest of the trial, which is expected to last at least through January. The trial will decide how to apportion liability in the crash so attorneys representing more than 75 plaintiffs can proceed with lawsuits.
