'' said Mrs. <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON>, adding that the doctors then sent the girl back to her room. `` It was wonderful. <PERSON> Penny </PERSON> did n't hesitate for an instant,'' <PERSON> Jason </PERSON>'s mother said. `` Circumstances brought us all together at the same time,'' Mrs. <PERSON> Point </PERSON> said. `` All those circumstances fitting together ... a movie script could n't be more bizarre than this.'' `` At the time my body was numb,'' said Mrs. <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON>. `` There was just no other way to do it.'' <PERSON> Jason </PERSON> was born with intrahepatic hypoplasia, which means the liver was too small for his body and functioned at only 2 percent. <PERSON> Candi </PERSON> was also born with a birth defect. Both children had received their first liver transplants in their first year of life.
