nology to upgrade its obsolete arsenal. <ORGANIZATION> Aeritalia </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Italy </LOCATION> supplied avionics technology for <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>'s new A5-M fighter plane, which recently had a successful test flight. <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> and British companies also have cooperated in updating Chinese tanks and planes. <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>'s strategy has been to use arms exports to subsidize improvements in its domestic arsenal that it could not otherwise afford. Its biggest market has been the <LOCATION> Middle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION>, where it has sold to both <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Iraq </LOCATION> during their 8-year-old border war.
