n against the guerrillas. Arrival of the new weapons prompted a guerrilla offensive along the strategic <LOCATION> Salang </LOCATION> highway that links <LOCATION> Kabul </LOCATION> with the Soviet border to the north. <PERSON> Ahmad </PERSON> <PERSON> Shah </PERSON> <PERSON> Masoud </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Jamiat-e-Islami </ORGANIZATION>'s commander in the <LOCATION> Panjshir </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Valley </LOCATION>, claims to have closed the highway but <PERSON> Shuaib </PERSON> of the <PERSON> Jamiat </PERSON> said reports from units along the road were sporadic and there was no recent confirmation that it remained closed. The <LOCATION> Salang </LOCATION> highway is the only overland route to the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION>.
