<TEXT>
 The first episode of `` War and Remembrance,'' the opening salvo from <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>'s big gun in the November ratings war, placed fourth in the weekly Nielsens, not good enough to prevent <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> from winning the week. The No. 1 show of the week was a one-hour episode of <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` The Cosby Show'' in which Cliff and <PERSON> Clair </PERSON> became grandparents. It had a 30.3 rating and a 47 share, the highest-rated `` Cosby'' since last March. <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> dominated the top 10 and won the week ending Nov. 12 with an average, prime-time rating of 15.6. <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> was second with 14.0 and CBS third with 11.5. Each rating point equals 904,000 homes with television. The share is a percentage of sets in use. `` War and Remembrance'' opened Sunday with a 21.8 rating and a 31 share. The national rating, released Tuesday, was lower than the 17-city overnights available Monday. The first installment's rating reportedly met <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>'s guarantee to sponsors, but the network was somewhat disappointed since ratings for multi-episode miniseries often start and finish at a high but sag in the middle. The miniseries is a sequel to `` The Winds of War,'' which opened in 1983 with a rating of 39.1 and a 53 share. `` War and Remembrance'' runs 18 hours in seven parts, but the story does n't conclude until sometime next year when <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> is scheduled to run the rest of the 32-hour World War II saga. Because of delays in its other programming due to the writers' strike, <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> rushed the first part of the miniseries to air this month, one of four ratings `` sweeps'' periods each year when network affiliate ratings are measured Originally the entire 32 hours was to have run in 1989. The 10 top-rated shows of the week were: `` The Cosby Show,'' `` Cheers'' and `` Golden Girls,'' <ORGANI