<TEXT>
 <LOCATION> Malaysia </LOCATION> is studying whether to participate in the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION>'s space program, a move that would cost $ 10 million, a government official said Tuesday. Considering the cost, Science, Technology and Environment Minister <PERSON> Amar </PERSON> <PERSON> Stephen </PERSON> <PERSON> Yong </PERSON> said the matter needed further study, as well as Cabinet approval. There are 22 Malaysian applicants to fly in space, and four would be selected for further training to become a cosmonaut, he said. `` We have to ascertain whether our participation in the program would benefit the nation in any way and therefore a detailed study was necessary,'' he said.
