<HEAD>Arab, Moslem Countries Recognize New State; Europe Cautious</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By NEIL MacFARQUHAR</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 At least 13 nations recognized the <LOCATION> Palestinian </LOCATION> state declared Tuesday, most of them Arab or Moslem backers of the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION>, but <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION> was cautious and <LOCATION> Palestinians </LOCATION> opposed to <PERSON> Yasser </PERSON> <PERSON> Arafat </PERSON> condemned the move. <PERSON> Javier </PERSON> <PERSON> Perez </PERSON> <PERSON> de </PERSON> <PERSON> Cuellar </PERSON>, the <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> secretary-general, welcomed the decision by the <ORGANIZATION> Palestine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION> to recognize <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>'s right to exist and said it opens `` fresh opportunities. for progress towards peace.'' Countries recognizing the state included <LOCATION> Algeria </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Bahrain </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Iraq </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Jordan </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Kuwait </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Tunisia </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Saudia </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Arabia </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Yemen </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Malaysia </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Mauritania </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Turkey </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Indonesia </LOCATION>. <LOCATION> Egypt </LOCATION>, the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Arab </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Emirates </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Morocco </LOCATION> stopped short of extending diplomatic recognition but said they supported the move by <PERSON> Arafat </PERSON>, chairman of the <ORGANIZATION> Palestine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION>, and the <ORGANIZATION> Palestine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION>, which acts as the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> legislature. Foreign Minister <PERSON> Esmat </PERSON> <PERSON> Abdel-Meguid </PERSON> of <LOCATION>