<HEAD>State Board Delays Action on AMA Request to Ban `Smokeless
Cigarette'</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By ARTHUR H. ROTSTEIN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>TUCSON, Ariz. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <ORGANIZATION> Arizona </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pharmacy </ORGANIZATION> on Tuesday decided it would n't act on the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Medical </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION>'s request that it stop distribution of a new `` smokeless cigarette. The <ORGANIZATION> R.J. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Reynolds </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> is test marketing Premier cigarettes in <LOCATION> Phoenix </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Tucson </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Louis </LOCATION>. The <ORGANIZATION> AMA </ORGANIZATION> filed a petition Nov. 2 seeking to have the product declared a new and hazardous drug, the distribution of which then would fall under the auspices of the pharmaceutical board. `` Our obligation is to protect the public health, so we feel that something needs to be done about this,'' said <PERSON> Norma </PERSON> <PERSON> E. </PERSON> <PERSON> McConnell </PERSON>, president of the board. But the board `` will not in the morning make a decision that ` yes it is a drug' or ` no it is n't,' but we are working toward that,'' she said. Mrs. <PERSON> McConnell </PERSON> said the board hopes to get more information from the <ORGANIZATION> federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Food </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Drug </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Administration </ORGANIZATION>, which regulates distribution and marketing of drugs in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> and has more facilities and expertise that the state board. A petition the <ORGANIZATION> AMA </ORGANIZATION> filed with the <ORGANIZATION> FDA </ORGANIZATION> in April is pending. If the <LOCATION> Arizona </LOCATION> board later decides the cigarette is a drug, its options include seeking an injunction, such as the <ORGANIZATION> AMA </ORGANIZATION> sug