<DATELINE>OSAGE BEACH, Mo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The Missouri Baptist Convention says it `` respects, honors and intends to preserve'' emphasis on the priesthood of the believer _ a concept discounted to some extent by the national Southern Baptist Convention. The doctrine holds that each member has equal standing in interpreting Scripture and in other religious rights, but the national convention had insisted the pastor had ruling authority.
