<DATELINE>MANSFIELD, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Many of the hymns sung in present-day churches derive from a religious revival in 17th century <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>, the `` Great Awakening,'' says a <ORGANIZATION> Protestant </ORGANIZATION> campus chaplain at <ORGANIZATION> Manfield </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION>. Based on research, the Rev. <PERSON> Joanne </PERSON> <PERSON> Weiss </PERSON> says that before that period, church music primarily was chanted psalms. `` The change from psalms to hymns took place because worshipers needed a new language of praise,'' she says.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>DENVER (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
