<HEAD>Energy Futures Prices Higher In Quiet Trading</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Energy futures prices have moved higher in quiet trading led by refined products. The December contract for unleaded gasoline rose 1.51 cents to 48.16 cents a gallon on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mercantile </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>. The December contract for heating oil increased 0.62 cent to 44.63 cents a gallon. Other contract months for oil and gasoline also advanced. The December contract for <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> Intermediate, the benchmark grade of <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> crude oil, closed at $ 14.27 per barrel, up 32 cents from Friday's settlement price. Other contract months also gained. Traders said activity was light, with many participants attending the annual meeting of the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Petroleum </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Institute </ORGANIZATION> here. Executives from major oil companies are represented at the three-day meeting in addition to analysts, scientists and government officials. Speakers at the meeting, attended by more than 1,000 oil industry officials, were not optimistic about the prospects that <ORGANIZATION> OPEC </ORGANIZATION> would reach an agreement on limiting crude production at its upcoming meeting. Analysts had forecast a firming of prices in advance of two meetings involving members of the <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Petroleum </ORGANIZATION> Exporting Countries. <ORGANIZATION> OPEC </ORGANIZATION>'s price and strategy committees are scheduled to meet on Thursday followed by the full meeting of all 13 ministers next Monday. Opinion is divided over what <ORGANIZATION> OPEC </ORGANIZATION> might accomplish, but the hope is that the cartel will move closer to an agreement that would curtail production among its members and help boost world oil prices.
