gn and handle the policy. That was a rarity for <ORGANIZATION> Chubb </ORGANIZATION>, and unlikely to happen again, said <PERSON> Lewis </PERSON>. The company has said Good Weather exceeded its authority in offering more than $ 40 million in insurance. `` I think they'll be more careful with how they -LRB- deal -RRB- with managing general agents,'' said Ms. <PERSON> Manning </PERSON> said. Eventually, <PERSON> Lewis </PERSON> said, `` Wall Street will forget about -LRB- the controversy -RRB- and concentrate on 1989 numbers.'' <ORGANIZATION> Chubb </ORGANIZATION> is not contemplating offering a similar type of drought insurance next year, said company spokeswoman <PERSON> Gail </PERSON> <PERSON> Devlin </PERSON>. She said it was not appropriate to discuss plans beyond that.
