<DATELINE>PHOENIX (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Ramada </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> shareholders will get cash payments of $ 7 per share under a restructuring that will see the sale of the company's <ORGANIZATION> Ramada </ORGANIZATION> and Rodeway hotel businesses and its restaurant operations. In a statement mailed Monday to its shareholders, <PERSON> Ramada </PERSON> provided details of a plan it announced in October to thwart a proposed buy-out by the company's biggest stockholder, the <PERSON> Pritzker </PERSON> family of <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION>. After completing the restructuring, <ORGANIZATION> Ramada </ORGANIZATION> will be left with its casino operations in <LOCATION> Nevada </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION>, which already provide a major share of its operating revenue. `` The purpose of the plan is to enable you to realize a near-term return on your investment and provide you with a continuing stake in <ORGANIZATION> Ramada </ORGANIZATION>'s profitable gaming business,'' said <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Snell </PERSON>, <PERSON> Ramada </PERSON> board chairman, in a letter accompanying the statement to stockholders. Ramada stock closed down 37 -LCB- cents a share to $ 8.87 -LCB- in composite <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> trading on Monday. <PERSON> Jay </PERSON> <PERSON> Pritzker </PERSON>, president of <ORGANIZATION> HCC </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, an affiliate of the <ORGANIZATION> Pritzkers </ORGANIZATION>' Hyatt hotel chain, offered $ 10 a share for Ramada in early September. Ramada rejected the $ 368 million offer as unfair to shareholders. `` It is our firm conviction that a sale of control of the company at this time is not in the best interests of the company, its shareholders and other affected constituents,'' <PERSON> Snell </PERSON> said. Ramada operates <ORGA