<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Stocks advanced marginally Tuesday and volume fell to the lowest level in seven weeks, reflecting investor reluctance to participate ahead of the government's potentially market-jolting monthly trade report. Brokers said buying was largely limited to the components of the <ORGANIZATION> Dow </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Jones </ORGANIZATION> industrial average, which finished with a 12.09 gain to 2,077.17, snapping a four-session losing streak. Most broader market barometers nudged higher. The <ORGANIZATION> Commerce </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> was due to report the September merchandise trade balance Wednesday morning and most expectations were for a $ 10.5 billion shortfall. If the deficit number substantially exceeds that amount, some fear it could trigger a selloff in the dollar, stock and bond markets. `` Everybody's just waiting to see what those numbers are going to do,'' said <PERSON> Edward </PERSON> <PERSON> P. </PERSON> <PERSON> Nicoski </PERSON>, a technical analyst at <ORGANIZATION> Piper </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Jaffray </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Hopwood </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, a Minneapolis-based investment firm. Although the huge trade deficits racked up by the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> can vary widely from month to month, they remain one of the most powerful market movers and have become a symbol of American economic weakness. Despite widespread reluctance by investors to participate in the stock market ahead of the trade-number release, some Wall Street strategists said the conditions have been laid for some gains over the next several days. `` I think barring something totally unforeseen in terms of a negative trade number, we're setting ourselves up for a fairly significant rally,'' said <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Conlon </PERSON>, executive vice president and director of equity research at <ORGANIZATION> Nikko </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>. International in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> `` There's been a lot of liquidation over the last week or so by traders and a good deal of skepticism in the market,'' he said. `` That's a potent combination for stocks to go up.'' Others were more cautious, based on technical analyses that showed a lack of demand for stocks. `` We're oversold enough to give us a pop, but based on breadth, I really do n't think we'll get much to the upside,'' <PERSON> Nicoski </PERSON> said. Advancing issues barely outnumbered declines in nationwide trading of <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> Exchange-listed stocks, with 715 up, 709 down and 534 unchanged. Volume on the <ORGANIZATION> NYSE </ORGANIZATION> floor totaled 115.17 million shares, down from 142.90 million in the previous session. It was the lowest level of trading since a 113.72 million-share day Sept. 28. Nationwide, consolidated volume in NYSE-listed issues, including trading at regional exchanges and on the over-the-counter market, totaled 137.24 million shares. Prime Computer led the <ORGANIZATION> NYSE </ORGANIZATION>'s most-active list, rising 1 ~ to 17 -RCB- on volume of 2.3 million shares <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> investor <PERSON> Bennet </PERSON> <PERSON> Lebow </PERSON> undertook a $ 20 a share offer for the company. <ORGANIZATION> J.C. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Penney </ORGANIZATION> rose 1 to 53 after it reported third-quarter earnings that exceeded expectations. Among other retailers, <PERSON> Dayton </PERSON> <PERSON> Hudson </PERSON> rose -RRB- to 39 | after it reported a 35 percent gain in third-quarter earnings Among gaining blue chips, <ORGANIZATION> Woolworth </ORGANIZATION> rose ~ to 51 \, <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZA